description: Deletes an existing default sender ID on a configuration set. A default sender ID is the identity that appears on recipients' devices when they receive SMS messages. Support for sender ID capabilities varies by country or region.

parameters.name: ConfigurationSetName
parameters.description: The name of the configuration set or the configuration set Amazon Resource Name (ARN) to delete the default sender ID from. The ConfigurationSetName and ConfigurationSetArn can be found using the  DescribeConfigurationSets action.

nested_items.name: ConfigurationSetArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the configuration set.

nested_items.name: ConfigurationSetName
nested_items.description: The name of the configuration set.

nested_items.name: SenderId
nested_items.description: The current sender ID for the configuration set.
